Specificity is calculated based on a four-part value in the format (a, b, c, d):

a: Inline styles (added to an element in the "style" attribute) - 1000 points
b: IDs - 100 points
c: Classes, attributes, and pseudo-classes - 10 points
d: Elements and pseudo-elements - 1 point

Types of Selectors and Their Specificity
Inline Styles

style="property: value;"
Specificity: (1, 0, 0, 0)
ID Selectors

#id
Specificity: (0, 1, 0, 0)
Class Selectors

.class
Specificity: (0, 0, 1, 0)
Attribute Selectors

[attribute]
Specificity: (0, 0, 1, 0)
Pseudo-classes

:pseudo-class (e.g., :hover, :nth-child)
Specificity: (0, 0, 1, 0)
Element Selectors

element (e.g., div, p, h1)
Specificity: (0, 0, 0, 1)
Pseudo-elements

::pseudo-element (e.g., ::before, ::after)
Specificity: (0, 0, 0, 1)